snippet.textDisplay:
this bengali/ assamese is so myopic.. Let me clear at the start.. I am an Assamese whose mother tongue is bengali..go figure.. Goalpara is indeed a district of Assam...why this sounds more bengali than assamese. is because this is more naer to the cultural ethos of rangpur/dinajpur/coochbehar and the contigous area.. People of these areas are basically bengali by mother tongue but have deep assamese influences being in the region and part of the assam and greater assames kingdom..

So if a bengali things .. its a bengali song-- he is perefctly right..its predominantly a song in bangla..and if an assamese things its an assamese song.. he sure can claim that too for it comes form the land of our assam..but yes the language is bangla for the most..

I mean I m a bengali --but from Assam and very proud of that--- its a song of our state..Bangla doesnt belong to the prsent day bangaldesh or WB only...Bangladeshi and WB bengalis cannot appropriate all bengalis..

Dont try hijack my identity... I m equaly proud and comfortable in both.

-----------
